--Mush--

Mush is a program that display a composite sprite at the screen.
You can run it with FCEUX emulator.

Composite Sprite?
Yes, the mushroom is composed of 4 sprites/tiles 8x8:

+---------++---------+
|      000||000      |
|     0111||1110     |
|    01111||11110    |
|   011111||111110   |
|  0111111||1111110  |
| 01111111||11111110 |
|011111111||111111110|
|011111111||111111110|
+---------++---------+
+---------++---------+
|  0222202||2022220  |
|  0222202||2022220  |
|  0222202||2022220  |
|  0222222||2222220  |
|   022222||222220   |
|    00000||00000    |
|         ||         |
|         ||         |
+---------++---------+

All tiles can have 3 colors or less: 0, 1, 2 or 3.
Colors are defined in the SprPalette.

Tiles are defined in tiles.spr:
$0, Sprite 1
$1, Sprite 2
$2, Sprite 3
$3  Sprite 4

All tiles are diplayed in a way that it feels like there's only one.

Note that I could use only 2 tiles and use them by turning them horizontally.

